This class provides the validation mechanism for Swing components.

This class provides the validation mechanism for Swing components. GUIs often need to ensure that the components are in a valid state before allowing the user to navigate the input focus. To do this, clients create a subclass of InputVerifier and, using JComponent's setInputVerifier method, attach an instance of their subclass to the JComponent which is the source of the focus transfer operation. The InputVerifier also provides the possibility to validate against the target of the focus transfer which may reject the focus. Before focus is transferred from the source Swing component to the target Swing component, the input verifier's shouldYieldFocus(source, target) method is called. Focus is transferred only if that method returns true.

trans-unit.source: This class represents image data which is stored in a band interleaved fashion and for which each sample of a pixel occupies one data element of the DataBuffer.

This class represents image data which is stored in a band interleaved fashion and for which each sample of a pixel occupies one data element of the DataBuffer. It subclasses ComponentSampleModel but provides a more efficient implementation for accessing band interleaved image data than is provided by ComponentSampleModel. This class should typically be used when working with images which store sample data for each band in a different bank of the DataBuffer. Accessor methods are provided so that image data can be manipulated directly. Pixel stride is the number of data array elements between two samples for the same band on the same scanline. The pixel stride for a BandedSampleModel is one. Scanline stride is the number of data array elements between a given sample and the corresponding sample in the same column of the next scanline. Band offsets denote the number of data array elements from the first data array element of the bank of the DataBuffer holding each band to the first sample of the band. The bands are numbered from 0 to N-1. Bank indices denote the correspondence between a bank of the data buffer and a band of image data. This class supports TYPE_BYTE, TYPE_USHORT, TYPE_SHORT, TYPE_INT, TYPE_FLOAT, and TYPE_DOUBLE datatypes
This class represents image data which is stored in a pixel interleaved fashion and for which each sample of a pixel occupies one data element of the DataBuffer.

This class represents image data which is stored in a pixel interleaved fashion and for which each sample of a pixel occupies one data element of the DataBuffer. It subclasses ComponentSampleModel but provides a more efficient implementation for accessing pixel interleaved image data than is provided by ComponentSampleModel. This class stores sample data for all bands in a single bank of the DataBuffer. Accessor methods are provided so that image data can be manipulated directly. Pixel stride is the number of data array elements between two samples for the same band on the same scanline. Scanline stride is the number of data array elements between a given sample and the corresponding sample in the same column of the next scanline. Band offsets denote the number of data array elements from the first data array element of the bank of the DataBuffer holding each band to the first sample of the band. The bands are numbered from 0 to N-1. Bank indices denote the correspondence between a bank of the data buffer and a band of image data. This class supports TYPE_BYTE, TYPE_USHORT, TYPE_SHORT, TYPE_INT, TYPE_FLOAT and TYPE_DOUBLE datatypes.
This class represents image data which is stored such that each sample of a pixel occupies one data element of the DataBuffer.

This class represents image data which is stored such that each sample of a pixel occupies one data element of the DataBuffer. It stores the N samples which make up a pixel in N separate data array elements. Different bands may be in different banks of the DataBuffer. This class can support different kinds of interleaving, e.g. band interleaving, scanline interleaving, and pixel interleaving. This class supports either or both a default exclusive mode and a shared mode. When acquired in exclusive mode, attempted acquires by other threads cannot succeed. Shared mode acquires by multiple threads may (but need not) succeed. This class does not "understand" these differences except in the mechanical sense that when a shared mode acquire succeeds, the next waiting thread (if one exists) must also determine whether it can acquire as well. Threads waiting in the different modes share the same FIFO queue. Usually, implementation subclasses support only one of these modes, but both can come into play for example in a ReadWriteLock. Subclasses that support only exclusive or only shared modes need not define the methods supporting the unused mode.
trans-unit.target: Esta clase admite un modo exclusivo predeterminado y un modo compartido o ambos . Cuando se adquiere en modo exclusivo, los intentos de adquisición por otros subprocesos no pueden tener éxito. El modo compartido adquirido por varios subprocesos puede (pero no es necesario) tener éxito. Esta clase no "comprende" estas diferencias excepto en el sentido mecánico de que cuando una adquisición en modo compartido tiene éxito, el siguiente hilo en espera (si existe) también debe determinar si puede adquirir también. Por lo general, las subclases de implementación admiten solo uno de estos modos, pero ambos pueden entrar en juego, por ejemplo, en un ReadWriteLock . This class uses 32-bit integers to store its location and dimensions. Frequently operations may produce a result that exceeds the range of a 32-bit integer. The methods will calculate their results in a way that avoids any 32-bit overflow for intermediate results and then choose the best representation to store the final results back into the 32-bit fields which hold the location and dimensions. The location of the result will be stored into the x and y fields by clipping the true result to the nearest 32-bit value. The values stored into the width and height dimension fields will be chosen as the 32-bit values that encompass the largest part of the true result as possible. Generally this means that the dimension will be clipped independently to the range of 32-bit integers except that if the location had to be moved to store it into its pair of 32-bit fields then the dimensions will be adjusted relative to the "best representation" of the location. If the true result had a negative dimension and was therefore non-existent along one or both axes, the stored dimensions will be negative numbers in those axes. If the true result had a location that could be represented within the range of 32-bit integers, but zero dimension along one or both axes, then the stored dimensions will be zero in those axes.

This exception is thrown by VirtualMachine.loadAgent or VirtualMachine.loadAgentLibrary, loadAgentPath methods if the agent, or agent library, cannot be loaded.

This exception is thrown by VirtualMachine.loadAgent, VirtualMachine.loadAgentLibrary, VirtualMachine.loadAgentPath methods if an agent, or agent library, cannot be initialized. When thrown by VirtualMachine.loadAgentLibrary, or VirtualMachine.loadAgentPath then the exception encapsulates the error returned by the agent's Agent_OnAttach function. This error code can be obtained by invoking the returnValue method.

This exception is thrown by doPrivileged(PrivilegedExceptionAction) and doPrivileged(PrivilegedExceptionAction, AccessControlContext context) to indicate that the action being performed threw a checked exception.
trans-unit.target: Esta excepción es lanzada por doPrivileged(PrivilegedExceptionAction) y doPrivileged(PrivilegedExceptionAction, AccessControlContext context) para indicar que la acción que se está realizando arrojó una excepción marcada.

trans-unit.source: This exception is thrown by doPrivileged(PrivilegedExceptionAction) and doPrivileged(PrivilegedExceptionAction, AccessControlContext context) to indicate that the action being performed threw a checked exception. The exception thrown by the action can be obtained by calling the getException method. In effect, an PrivilegedActionException is a "wrapper" for an exception thrown by a privileged action.
trans-unit.target: Esta excepción es lanzada por doPrivileged(PrivilegedExceptionAction) y doPrivileged(PrivilegedExceptionAction, AccessControlContext context) para indicar que la acción que se está realizando arrojó una excepción marcada. La excepción lanzada por la acción se puede obtener llamando al método getException . En efecto, una PrivilegedActionException es un "contenedor" para una excepción generada por una acción privilegiada.

trans-unit.source: This exception is thrown by LoginModules if authentication failed. For example, a LoginModule throws this exception if the user entered an incorrect password.
trans-unit.target: LoginModules lanza esta excepción si falla la autenticación. Por ejemplo, un LoginModule lanza esta excepción si el usuario ingresó una contraseña incorrecta.

trans-unit.source: This exception is thrown by LoginModules when they determine that a Credential has expired. For example, a LoginModule authenticating a user in its login method may determine that the user's password, although entered correctly, has expired. In this case the LoginModule throws this exception to notify the application. The application can then take the appropriate steps to assist the user in updating the password.
trans-unit.target: LoginModules lanza esta excepción cuando determinan que una Credential ha expirado. Por ejemplo, un LoginModule que autentica a un usuario en su método de login puede determinar que la contraseña del usuario, aunque ingresada correctamente, ha expirado. En este caso, LoginModule lanza esta excepción para notificar a la aplicación. La aplicación puede entonces tomar los pasos apropiados para ayudar al usuario a actualizar la contraseña.

trans-unit.source: This exception is thrown by LoginModules when they determine that an account has expired. For example, a LoginModule, after successfully authenticating a user, may determine that the user's account has expired. In this case the LoginModule throws this exception to notify the application. The application can then take the appropriate steps to notify the user.
trans-unit.target: LoginModules lanza esta excepción cuando determinan que una cuenta ha expirado. Por ejemplo, un LoginModule , después de autenticar exitosamente a un usuario, puede determinar que la cuenta del usuario ha expirado. En este caso, LoginModule lanza esta excepción para notificar a la aplicación. Luego, la aplicación puede tomar los pasos apropiados para notificar al usuario.

trans-unit.source: This exception is thrown by a SASL mechanism implementation to indicate that the SASL exchange has failed due to reasons related to authentication, such as an invalid identity, passphrase, or key.
trans-unit.target: Esta excepción es lanzada por una implementación del mecanismo SASL para indicar que el intercambio SASL ha fallado debido a razones relacionadas con la autenticación,como una identidad,frase de contraseña o clave inválida.

trans-unit.source: This exception is thrown by credentials implementing the Destroyable interface when the destroy method fails.
trans-unit.target: Esta excepción es lanzada por credenciales que implementan la interfaz Destroyable cuando falla el método de destroy .

trans-unit.source: This exception is thrown by credentials implementing the Refreshable interface when the refresh method fails.
trans-unit.target: Esta excepción es lanzada por credenciales que implementan la interfaz Refreshable cuando falla el método de refresh .

trans-unit.source: This exception is thrown by methods to indicate that a binding cannot be added because the name is already bound to another object.
trans-unit.target: Esta excepción es lanzada por los métodos para indicar que no se puede añadir una vinculación porque el nombre ya está vinculado a otro objeto.

trans-unit.source: This exception is thrown by the AccessController to indicate that a requested access (to a critical system resource such as the file system or the network) is denied.
trans-unit.target: Esta excepción es lanzada por el AccessController para indicar que se deniega un acceso solicitado (a un recurso crítico del sistema como el sistema de archivos o la red).

trans-unit.source: This exception is thrown by the RMI runtime when activation fails during a remote call to an activatable object.
This exception is thrown by various methods in the java.awt.dnd package.

This exception is thrown by various methods in the java.awt.dnd package. It is usually thrown to indicate that the target in question is unable to undertake the requested operation that the present time, since the underlying DnD system is not in the appropriate state.
This exception is thrown if a key in the keystore cannot be recovered.
trans-unit.target: Esta excepción se lanza si no se puede recuperar una llave en el almacén de llaves.

trans-unit.source: This exception is thrown if an entry in the keystore cannot be recovered.
trans-unit.target: Esta excepción se lanza si no se puede recuperar una entrada en el almacén de llaves.

trans-unit.source: This exception is thrown if the native CMM returns an error.
This exception is thrown to indicate that the operation reached a point in the name where the operation cannot proceed any further.
trans-unit.target: Esta excepción se lanza para indicar que la operación llegó a un punto en el nombre en el que la operación no puede seguir adelante.

trans-unit.source: This exception is thrown to indicate that the operation reached a point in the name where the operation cannot proceed any further. When performing an operation on a composite name, a naming service provider may reach a part of the name that does not belong to its namespace. At that point, it can construct a CannotProceedException and then invoke methods provided by javax.naming.spi.NamingManager (such as getContinuationContext()) to locate another provider to continue the operation. If this is not possible, this exception is raised to the caller of the context operation.
trans-unit.target: Esta excepción se lanza para indicar que la operación llegó a un punto en el nombre en el que la operación no puede seguir adelante.Al realizar una operación en un nombre compuesto,un proveedor de servicios de denominación puede llegar a una parte del nombre que no pertenezca a su espacio de nombres.En ese momento,puede construir una excepción de CannotProceed y luego invocar los métodos proporcionados por javax.naming.spi.NamingManager (como getContinuationContext())para localizar otro proveedor que continúe la operación.Si esto no es posible,esta excepción se eleva al llamador de la operación de contexto.

trans-unit.source: This exception is thrown to indicate that the result being returned or returned so far is partial, and that the operation cannot be completed.
trans-unit.target: Esta excepción se lanza para indicar que el resultado que se está devolviendo o que se ha devuelto hasta ahora es parcial,y que la operación no puede ser completada.

trans-unit.source: This exception is thrown to indicate that the result being returned or returned so far is partial, and that the operation cannot be completed. For example, when listing a context, this exception indicates that returned results only represents some of the bindings in the context.
trans-unit.target: Esta excepción se lanza para indicar que el resultado que se está devolviendo o que se ha devuelto hasta ahora es parcial,y que la operación no puede ser completada.Por ejemplo,cuando se enumera un contexto,esta excepción indica que los resultados devueltos sólo representan algunas de las encuadernaciones del contexto.

trans-unit.source: This exception is thrown when JarSigner.sign(java.util.zip.ZipFile, java.io.OutputStream) fails.
This exception is thrown when a Cipher operating in an AEAD mode (such as GCM/CCM) is unable to verify the supplied authentication tag.
trans-unit.target: Esta excepción se produce cuando un Cipher funciona en un modo AEAD (como GCM / CCM) no puede verificar la etiqueta de autenticación proporcionada.

trans-unit.source: This exception is thrown when a call is received that does not match the available skeleton. It indicates either that the remote method names or signatures in this interface have changed or that the stub class used to make the call and the skeleton receiving the call were not generated by the same version of the stub compiler (rmic).

This exception is thrown when a call is received that does not match the available skeleton. It indicates either that the remote method names or signatures in this interface have changed or that the stub class used to make the call and the skeleton receiving the call were not generated by the same version of the stub protocol.
This exception is thrown when a component of the name cannot be resolved because it is not bound.
trans-unit.target: Esta excepción se lanza cuando un componente del nombre no puede resolverse porque no está ligado.

trans-unit.source: This exception is thrown when a context implementation does not support the operation being invoked.
trans-unit.target: Esta excepción se lanza cuando la aplicación del contexto no apoya la operación que se invoca.

trans-unit.source: This exception is thrown when a context implementation does not support the operation being invoked. For example, if a server does not support the Context.bind() method it would throw OperationNotSupportedException when the bind() method is invoked on it.
trans-unit.target: Esta excepción se lanza cuando la aplicación del contexto no apoya la operación que se invoca.Por ejemplo,si un servidor no soporta el método Context.bind()lanzará OperationNotSupportedException cuando se invoque el método bind()en él.

trans-unit.source: This exception is thrown when a loop was detected while attempting to resolve a link, or an implementation specific limit on link counts has been reached.
This exception is thrown when a loop was detected will attempting to resolve a link, or an implementation specific limit on link counts has been reached.
trans-unit.target: Esta excepción se lanza cuando se detecta un bucle que intenta resolver un enlace,o se ha alcanzado un límite específico de aplicación en el recuento de enlaces.

trans-unit.source: This exception is thrown when a malformed link was encountered while resolving or constructing a link.
trans-unit.target: Esta excepción se lanza cuando se encuentra un eslabón malformado mientras se resuelve o se construye un eslabón.

trans-unit.source: This exception is thrown when a method does not terminate within the specified time limit.
trans-unit.target: Esta excepción se lanza cuando un método no termina dentro del plazo especificado.

trans-unit.source: This exception is thrown when a method does not terminate within the specified time limit. This can happen, for example, if the user specifies that the method should take no longer than 10 seconds, and the method fails to complete with 10 seconds.
trans-unit.target: Esta excepción se lanza cuando un método no termina dentro del plazo especificado.Esto puede ocurrir,por ejemplo,si el usuario especifica que el método no debe tardar más de 10 segundos y el método no termina con 10 segundos.

trans-unit.source: This exception is thrown when a method in some ways violates the schema.
trans-unit.target: Esta excepción se lanza cuando un método de alguna manera viola el esquema.

trans-unit.source: This exception is thrown when a method in some ways violates the schema. An example of schema violation is modifying attributes of an object that violates the object's schema definition. Another example is renaming or moving an object to a part of the namespace that violates the namespace's schema definition.
trans-unit.target: Esta excepción se lanza cuando un método de alguna manera viola el esquema.Un ejemplo de violación del esquema es la modificación de los atributos de un objeto que viola la definición del esquema del objeto.Otro ejemplo es el cambio de nombre o el desplazamiento de un objeto a una parte del espacio de nombres que infrinja la definición del esquema del espacio de nombres.

trans-unit.source: This exception is thrown when a method produces a result that exceeds a size-related limit.
trans-unit.target: Esta excepción se lanza cuando un método produce un resultado que supera un límite de tamaño.

trans-unit.source: This exception is thrown when a method produces a result that exceeds a size-related limit. This can happen, for example, if the result contains more objects than the user requested, or when the size of the result exceeds some implementation-specific limit.
trans-unit.target: Esta excepción se lanza cuando un método produce un resultado que supera un límite de tamaño.Esto puede ocurrir,por ejemplo,si el resultado contiene más objetos que los solicitados por el usuario,o cuando el tamaño del resultado supera algún límite específico de la aplicación.

trans-unit.source: This exception is thrown when a method terminates abnormally due to a user or system specified limit.
trans-unit.target: Esta excepción se lanza cuando un método termina anormalmente debido a un límite especificado por el usuario o el sistema.

trans-unit.source: This exception is thrown when a method terminates abnormally due to a user or system specified limit. This is different from a InsufficientResourceException in that LimitExceededException is due to a user/system specified limit. For example, running out of memory to complete the request would be an insufficient resource. The client asking for 10 answers and getting back 11 is a size limit exception.
trans-unit.target: Esta excepción se lanza cuando un método termina anormalmente debido a un límite especificado por el usuario o el sistema.Esto es diferente de una excepción de insuficiencia de recursos en que la excepción de límite excedido se debe a un límite especificado por el usuario o el sistema.Por ejemplo,quedarse sin memoria para completar la solicitud sería un recurso insuficiente.El cliente que pide 10 respuestas y obtiene 11 es una excepción al límite de tamaño.

trans-unit.source: This exception is thrown when a naming operation proceeds to a point where a context is required to continue the operation, but the resolved object is not a context.
trans-unit.target: Esta excepción se lanza cuando una operación de nombramiento procede hasta un punto en el que se requiere un contexto para continuar la operación,pero el objeto resuelto no es un contexto.

trans-unit.source: This exception is thrown when a naming operation proceeds to a point where a context is required to continue the operation, but the resolved object is not a context. For example, Context.destroy() requires that the named object be a context. If it is not, NotContextException is thrown. Another example is a non-context being encountered during the resolution phase of the Context methods.
trans-unit.target: Esta excepción se lanza cuando una operación de nombramiento procede hasta un punto en el que se requiere un contexto para continuar la operación,pero el objeto resuelto no es un contexto.Por ejemplo,Context.destroy()requiere que el objeto nombrado sea un contexto.Si no lo es,se lanza NotContextException.Otro ejemplo es un no-contexto que se encuentra durante la fase de resolución de los métodos Context.

trans-unit.source: This exception is thrown when a particular XML mechanism is requested but is not available in the environment.
This exception is thrown when a particular cryptographic algorithm is requested but is not available in the environment.
trans-unit.target: Esta excepción se lanza cuando se solicita un determinado algoritmo criptográfico pero no está disponible en el entorno.

trans-unit.source: This exception is thrown when a particular padding mechanism is expected for the input data but the data is not padded properly.
trans-unit.target: Esta excepción se da cuando se espera un mecanismo de acolchado particular para los datos de entrada pero los datos no están acolchados correctamente.

trans-unit.source: This exception is thrown when a particular padding mechanism is requested but is not available in the environment.
trans-unit.target: Esta excepción se lanza cuando se solicita un determinado mecanismo de acolchado pero no está disponible en el medio ambiente.

trans-unit.source: This exception is thrown when a particular security provider is requested but is not available in the environment.
trans-unit.target: Esta excepción se lanza cuando se solicita un determinado proveedor de seguridad pero no está disponible en el entorno.

trans-unit.source: This exception is thrown when an XML formatted string is being parsed into ModelMBean objects or when XML formatted strings are being created from ModelMBean objects.
trans-unit.target: Esta excepción se lanza cuando se analiza una cadena con formato XML en objetos ModelMBean o cuando se crean cadenas con formato XML a partir de objetos ModelMBean.

trans-unit.source: This exception is thrown when an XML formatted string is being parsed into ModelMBean objects or when XML formatted strings are being created from ModelMBean objects. It is also used to wrapper exceptions from XML parsers that may be used.
trans-unit.target: Esta excepción se lanza cuando se analiza una cadena con formato XML en objetos ModelMBean o cuando se crean cadenas con formato XML a partir de objetos ModelMBean.También se utiliza para envolver las excepciones de los analizadores XML que se pueden utilizar.

trans-unit.source: This exception is thrown when an attempt is made to add or modify an attribute set that has been specified incompletely or incorrectly.
trans-unit.target: Esta excepción se lanza cuando se intenta añadir o modificar un conjunto de atributos que se ha especificado de forma incompleta o incorrecta.

trans-unit.source: This exception is thrown when an attempt is made to add or modify an attribute set that has been specified incompletely or incorrectly. This could happen, for example, when attempting to add or modify a binding, or to create a new subcontext without specifying all the mandatory attributes required for creation of the object. Another situation in which this exception is thrown is by specification of incompatible attributes within the same attribute set, or attributes in conflict with that specified by the object's schema.
trans-unit.target: Esta excepción se lanza cuando se intenta añadir o modificar un conjunto de atributos que se ha especificado de forma incompleta o incorrecta.Esto podría ocurrir,por ejemplo,cuando se intenta añadir o modificar una vinculación,o crear un nuevo subcontexto sin especificar todos los atributos obligatorios necesarios para la creación del objeto.Otra situación en la que se lanza esta excepción es por la especificación de atributos incompatibles dentro del mismo conjunto de atributos,o atributos en conflicto con los especificados por el esquema del objeto.

trans-unit.source: This exception is thrown when an attempt is made to add to create an attribute with an invalid attribute identifier.
trans-unit.target: Esta excepción se lanza cuando se intenta añadir para crear un atributo con un identificador de atributo inválido.

trans-unit.source: This exception is thrown when an attempt is made to add to create an attribute with an invalid attribute identifier. The validity of an attribute identifier is directory-specific.
trans-unit.target: Esta excepción se lanza cuando se intenta añadir para crear un atributo con un identificador de atributo inválido.La validez de un identificador de atributo es específica de un directorio.

trans-unit.source: This exception is thrown when an attempt is made to add, or remove, or modify an attribute, its identifier, or its values that conflicts with the attribute's (schema) definition or the attribute's state.
trans-unit.target: Esta excepción se lanza cuando se intenta añadir,o eliminar,o modificar un atributo,su identificador o sus valores que entra en conflicto con la definición del atributo (esquema)o el estado del mismo.

trans-unit.source: This exception is thrown when an attempt is made to add, or remove, or modify an attribute, its identifier, or its values that conflicts with the attribute's (schema) definition or the attribute's state. It is thrown in response to DirContext.modifyAttributes(). It contains a list of modifications that have not been performed, in the order that they were supplied to modifyAttributes(). If the list is null, none of the modifications were performed successfully.
trans-unit.target: Esta excepción se lanza cuando se intenta añadir,o eliminar,o modificar un atributo,su identificador o sus valores que entra en conflicto con la definición del atributo (esquema)o el estado del mismo.Se lanza en respuesta a DirContext.modifyAttributes().Contiene una lista de las modificaciones que no se han realizado,en el orden en que fueron suministradas a modifyAttributes().Si la lista es nula,ninguna de las modificaciones se ha realizado con éxito.

trans-unit.source: This exception is thrown when an authentication error occurs while accessing the naming or directory service.
trans-unit.target: Esta excepción se lanza cuando se produce un error de autenticación al acceder al servicio de nombres o directorios.

trans-unit.source: This exception is thrown when an authentication error occurs while accessing the naming or directory service. An authentication error can happen, for example, when the credentials supplied by the user program are invalid or otherwise fail to authenticate the user to the naming/directory service.

This exception is thrown when an authentication error occurs while accessing the naming or directory service. An authentication error can happen, for example, when the credentials supplied by the user program is invalid or otherwise fails to authenticate the user to the naming/directory service.
trans-unit.target: Esta excepción se lanza cuando se produce un error de autenticación al acceder al servicio de nombres o directorios.Un error de autenticación puede ocurrir,por ejemplo,cuando las credenciales suministradas por el programa de usuario no son válidas o no se puede autenticar al usuario en el servicio de nombres o directorios.

trans-unit.source: This exception is thrown when an error occurs in accessing or processing an ICC_Profile object.
This exception is thrown when an error occurs in accessing or processing an ICC_Profile object.
This exception is thrown when an operation attempts to add an attribute that already exists.
trans-unit.target: Esta excepción se lanza cuando una operación intenta añadir un atributo que ya existe.

trans-unit.source: This exception is thrown when an output buffer provided by the user is too short to hold the operation result.
trans-unit.target: Esta excepción se lanza cuando una memoria intermedia de salida proporcionada por el usuario es demasiado corta para mantener el resultado de la operación.

trans-unit.source: This exception is thrown when attempting to access an attribute that does not exist.
trans-unit.target: Esta excepción se lanza cuando se intenta acceder a un atributo que no existe.

trans-unit.source: This exception is thrown when attempting to communicate with a directory or naming service and that service is not available.
trans-unit.target: Esta excepción se lanza cuando se intenta comunicar con un servicio de directorio o de nombres y ese servicio no está disponible.

trans-unit.source: This exception is thrown when attempting to communicate with a directory or naming service and that service is not available. It might be unavailable for different reasons. For example, the server might be too busy to service the request, or the server might not be registered to service any requests, etc.
trans-unit.target: Esta excepción se lanza cuando se intenta comunicar con un servicio de directorio o de nombres y ese servicio no está disponible.Puede que no esté disponible por diferentes razones.Por ejemplo,el servidor podría estar demasiado ocupado para atender la solicitud,o el servidor podría no estar registrado para atender ninguna solicitud,etc.

trans-unit.source: This exception is thrown when attempting to destroy a context that is not empty.
trans-unit.target: Esta excepción se lanza cuando se intenta destruir un contexto que no está vacío.

trans-unit.source: This exception is thrown when attempting to perform an operation for which the client has no permission.
trans-unit.target: Esta excepción se lanza cuando se intenta realizar una operación para la cual el cliente no tiene permiso.

trans-unit.source: This exception is thrown when attempting to perform an operation for which the client has no permission. The access control/permission model is dictated by the directory/naming server.
trans-unit.target: Esta excepción se lanza cuando se intenta realizar una operación para la cual el cliente no tiene permiso.El modelo de control de acceso/permiso es dictado por el servidor de directorio/nombre.

trans-unit.source: This exception is thrown when no initial context implementation can be created.
trans-unit.target: Esta excepción se lanza cuando no se puede crear una implementación de contexto inicial.

trans-unit.source: This exception is thrown when no initial context implementation can be created. The policy of how an initial context implementation is selected is described in the documentation of the InitialContext class.
trans-unit.target: Esta excepción se lanza cuando no se puede crear una implementación de contexto inicial.La política de cómo se selecciona una implementación de contexto inicial se describe en la documentación de la clase InitialContext.

trans-unit.source: This exception is thrown when resources are not available to complete the requested operation.
trans-unit.target: Esta excepción se da cuando no se dispone de recursos para completar la operación solicitada.

trans-unit.source: This exception is thrown when resources are not available to complete the requested operation. This might due to a lack of resources on the server or on the client. There are no restrictions to resource types, as different services might make use of different resources. Such restrictions might be due to physical limits and/or administrative quotas. Examples of limited resources are internal buffers, memory, network bandwidth.
trans-unit.target: Esta excepción se da cuando no se dispone de recursos para completar la operación solicitada.Esto puede deberse a la falta de recursos en el servidor o en el cliente.No hay restricciones en cuanto a los tipos de recursos,ya que diferentes servicios pueden hacer uso de diferentes recursos.Esas restricciones pueden deberse a límites físicos y/o cuotas administrativas.Ejemplos de recursos limitados son los buffers internos,la memoria,el ancho de banda de la red.

trans-unit.source: This exception is thrown when the client is unable to communicate with the directory or naming service.
trans-unit.target: Esta excepción se lanza cuando el cliente no puede comunicarse con el directorio o el servicio de nombres.

trans-unit.source: This exception is thrown when the client is unable to communicate with the directory or naming service. The inability to communicate with the service might be a result of many factors, such as network partitioning, hardware or interface problems, failures on either the client or server side. This exception is meant to be used to capture such communication problems.
trans-unit.target: Esta excepción se lanza cuando el cliente no puede comunicarse con el directorio o el servicio de nombres.La incapacidad de comunicarse con el servicio puede ser el resultado de muchos factores,como la partición de la red,problemas de hardware o de interfaz,fallos en el lado del cliente o del servidor.Esta excepción está destinada a utilizarse para captar esos problemas de comunicación.

trans-unit.source: This exception is thrown when the length of data provided to a block cipher is incorrect, i.e., does not match the block size of the cipher.
trans-unit.target: Esta excepción se lanza cuando la longitud de los datos proporcionados a un bloque de cifrado es incorrecta,es decir,no coincide con el tamaño del bloque del cifrado.

trans-unit.source: This exception is thrown when the naming operation being invoked has been interrupted.
trans-unit.target: Esta excepción se lanza cuando la operación de denominación que se invoca se ha interrumpido.

trans-unit.source: This exception is thrown when the naming operation being invoked has been interrupted. For example, an application might interrupt a thread that is performing a search. If the search supports being interrupted, it will throw InterruptedNamingException. Whether an operation is interruptible and when depends on its implementation (as provided by the service providers). Different implementations have different ways of protecting their resources and objects from being damaged due to unexpected interrupts.
trans-unit.target: Esta excepción se lanza cuando la operación de nombramiento que se invoca se ha interrumpido.Por ejemplo,una aplicación puede interrumpir un hilo que está realizando una búsqueda.Si la búsqueda admite ser interrumpida,lanzará InterruptedNamingException.El hecho de que una operación sea interrumpible y el momento en que lo sea depende de su implementación (según lo dispuesto por los proveedores de servicios).Las diferentes implementaciones tienen diferentes maneras de proteger sus recursos y objetos de ser dañados debido a interrupciones inesperadas.

trans-unit.source: This exception is thrown when the particular flavor of authentication requested is not supported.
trans-unit.target: Esta excepción se lanza cuando el sabor particular de la autenticación solicitada no está soportado.

trans-unit.source: This exception is thrown when the particular flavor of authentication requested is not supported. For example, if the program is attempting to use strong authentication but the directory/naming supports only simple authentication, this exception would be thrown. Identification of a particular flavor of authentication is provider- and server-specific. It may be specified using specific authentication schemes such those identified using SASL, or a generic authentication specifier (such as "simple" and "strong").

This flag bit indicates that the transform defined by this object performs a general scale in addition to the conversions indicated by other flag bits. This flag bit indicates that the transform defined by this object performs a mirror image flip about some axis which changes the normally right handed coordinate system into a left handed system in addition to the conversions indicated by other flag bits. A right handed coordinate system is one where the positive X axis rotates counterclockwise to overlay the positive Y axis similar to the direction that the fingers on your right hand curl when you stare end on at your thumb. A left handed coordinate system is one where the positive X axis rotates clockwise to overlay the positive Y axis similar to the direction that the fingers on your left hand curl. There is no mathematical way to determine the angle of the original flipping or mirroring transformation since all angles of flip are identical given an appropriate adjusting rotation.

trans-unit.source: This implementation checks to see that this node is the root; if so, it throws an appropriate exception. Then, it locks this node's parent, and calls a recursive helper method that traverses the subtree rooted at this node. The recursive method locks the node on which it was called, checks that it has not already been removed, and then ensures that all of its children are cached: The childrenNamesSpi() method is invoked and each returned child name is checked for containment in the child-cache. If a child is not already cached, the childSpi(String) method is invoked to create a Preferences instance for it, and this instance is put into the child-cache. Then the helper method calls itself recursively on each node contained in its child-cache. Next, it invokes removeNodeSpi(), marks itself as removed, and removes itself from its parent's child-cache. Finally, if there are any node change listeners, it enqueues a notification event for processing by the event dispatch thread.

trans-unit.target: Esta implementación verifica que este nodo sea la raíz; si es así, lanza una excepción apropiada. Luego, bloquea al padre de este nodo y llama a un método auxiliar recursivo que atraviesa el subárbol enraizado en este nodo. El método recursivo bloquea el nodo en el que fue llamado, verifica que aún no se haya eliminado y luego se asegura de que todos sus hijos estén almacenados en caché: Se invoca el método childrenNamesSpi() y se comprueba la contención de cada nombre de hijo devuelto en el caché de niños. Si un niño aún no está en caché, se invoca el método childSpi(String) para crear una instancia de Preferences para él, y esta instancia se coloca en el caché de niños. Luego, el método auxiliar se llama a sí mismo de forma recursiva en cada nodo contenido en su caché secundaria. A continuación, invoca removeNodeSpi() , se marca a sí mismo como eliminado y se elimina del caché secundario de su padre. Finalmente, si hay oyentes de cambio de nodo, pone en cola un evento de notificación para que lo procese el subproceso de despacho de eventos.

trans-unit.source: This implementation determines which is the smaller of this set and the specified collection, by invoking the size method on each. If this set has fewer elements, then the implementation iterates over this set, checking each element returned by the iterator in turn to see if it is contained in the specified collection. If it is so contained, it is removed from this set with the iterator's remove method. If the specified collection has fewer elements, then the implementation iterates over the specified collection, removing from this set each element returned by the iterator, using this set's remove method.
trans-unit.target: Esta implementación determina cuál es el más pequeño de este conjunto y la colección especificada, invocando el método de size en cada uno. Si este conjunto tiene menos elementos, la implementación itera sobre este conjunto, verificando cada elemento devuelto por el iterador a su vez para ver si está contenido en la colección especificada. Si está así contenido, se elimina de este conjunto con el método remove del iterador . Si la colección especificada tiene menos elementos, entonces la implementación itera sobre la colección especificada, eliminando de este conjunto cada elemento devuelto por el iterador, utilizando el método remove de este conjunto .

This implementation expects two sources of asynchronous notification. The timer thread fires asynchronously, and causes the caret to simply repaint the most recent bounding box. The caret also tracks change as the document is modified. Typically this will happen on the event dispatch thread as a result of some mouse or keyboard event. The caret behavior on both synchronous and asynchronous documents updates is controlled by UpdatePolicy property. The repaint of the new caret location will occur on the event thread in any case, as calls to modelToView are only safe on the event thread.
